The paper deals with deep neural networks and their optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, indicating computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the transfer of knowledge from one model to another, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves adversarial learning, which is a technique used in neural networks and falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as distillation and transfer learning, which are relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
